{
  "texts": [
    "The categories to be assigned were 'trust', 'fear', 'anticipation', 'anger', 'surprise', 'sadness', 'disgust', 'joy' and 'no emotion'.",
    "Reviewers matched the EmoLex assigned category on 29% of occasions.",
    "The inter-rater reliability was 0.786, indicating substantial agreement [101].",
    "Within this, between the reviewers, classifying tweets that the algorithm deemed as 'anger' caused the most disagreement, with the reviewers not matching on 5/11 occasions.",
    "Reviewers categorised these tweets as 'fear' or 'disgust' instead.Finally, the following reflections took place:Sunshine The efficient, rapid detection of tweets in a large dataset was a notable advantage, allowing for timely processing."
  ]
